{"bill":{"bill_id":1655217,"change_hash":"0eef21188e5f42f9f6c0a65bfdedd96e","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/SB1431\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+SB1431","completed":0,"status":2,"status_date":"2023-02-03","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-11","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-11","event":9},{"date":"2023-01-31","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-03","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-08","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-17","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-22","event":2}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"SB1431","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"S","body_id":8,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":7,"title":"Elected and certain appointed; procedure for removal by courts.","description":"Procedure for removal of elected and certain appointed officers by courts. Sets out the procedure by which, and clarifies the reasons for which, an elected officer or officer who has been appointed to fill an elective office may be removed from office. The bill requires, among other things, that (i) the general registrar review the petition and determine its sufficiency in accordance with the uniform standards approved by the State Board of Elections; (ii) the general registrar certify the petition within 10 business days and promptly file such certification with the clerk of the circuit court; and (iii) the certification state the number of signatures required, the number of signatures on the petition, and the number of valid signatures, along with any signatures found to be invalid and any material omissions from the petition. The bill also provides that the Commonwealth and the elected officer shall be the only two parties to a removal proceeding. This bill is a recommendation of the Boyd-Graves Conference.  Procedure for removal of elected and certain appointed officers by courts. Sets out the procedure by which, and clarifies the reasons for which, an elected officer or officer who has been appointed to fill an elective office may be removed from office. The bill requires, among other things, that (i) the general registrar review the petition and determine its sufficiency in accordance with the uniform standards approved by the State Board of Elections; (ii) the general registrar certify the petition within 10 business days and promptly file such certification with the clerk of the circuit court; and (iii) the certification state the number of signatures required, the number of signatures on the petition, and the number of valid signatures, along with any signatures found to be invalid and any material omissions from the petition. The bill also provides that the Commonwealth and the elected officer shall be the only two parties to a removal proceeding. This bill is a recommendation of the Boyd-Graves Conference.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-11","committee_id":167,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Privileges and Elections"},{"date":"2023-01-20","committee_id":4750,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Privileges and Elections: Subcommittee #1"},{"date":"2023-02-08","committee_id":156,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Privileges and Elections"},{"date":"2023-02-14","committee_id":3880,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Privileges and Elections: Subcommittee #2"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-11","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23100264D","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-11","action":"Referred to Committee on Privileges and Elections","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-20","action":"Assigned to P&E sub: Subcommittee #1","chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-31","action":"Reported from Privileges and Ele